MIDEX firmware blobs for the snd-usb-midex kernel module
=========================================================

This directory holds the firmware images uploaded by the kernel driver to
MIDEX devices that boot in their EZ-USB "no firmware" PID. See
../../../doc/firmware_upload_process.md for the full protocol and source
analysis.

Layout
------

  midex8.hex / midex8.fw     PID 0x1000 -> 0x1001 (MIDEX8 r1, AN2131)
  midex8r2.hex / midex8r2.fw PID 0x1010 -> 0x1001 (MIDEX8 r2, CY7C646 FX)
  midex3.hex / midex3.fw     PID 0x1100 -> 0x1101 (MIDEX3, CY7C646 FX)
  regenerate.sh              Maintainer-only: rebuilds the .hex and .fw

The .fw files are the kernel-ready packed-record format produced by
scripts/ihex2fw and consumed by request_ihex_firmware() inside the in-tree
ezusb helper (drivers/usb/misc/ezusb.c). Both the .hex sources and the .fw
outputs are checked in so end users do not need ihex2fw at install time.

../build.sh -i installs the three .fw files to /lib/firmware/midex/.
The driver requests them by the names "midex/midex8.fw" etc.

Regenerating
------------

If a primary source under ../../../doc/firmware/ changes, run:

    ./regenerate.sh

regenerate.sh needs the `ihex2fw` host tool. The easiest way to get it:

    wget -O /tmp/ihex2fw.c \
      https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/plain/tools/firmware/ihex2fw.c
    cc -O2 -o ~/.local/bin/ihex2fw /tmp/ihex2fw.c

regenerate.sh also accepts -k <kernel-source-dir> to pick up a tree-local
scripts/ihex2fw or tools/firmware/ihex2fw build.
